"advantages": "Infliximab is a well-established treatment for both ulcerative colitis and rheumatoid arthritis. It has been shown to be effective in multiple trials for both conditions. It targets the pro-inflammatory cytokine tumour necrosis factor- α (TNF -α), which is implicated in the pathogenesis of both diseases.",
"disadvantages": "Infliximab is administered via intravenous infusion, which may be inconvenient for some patients. It can also cause side effects such as infections, allergic reactions, and liver damage. It may not be suitable for patients with certain conditions such as heart failure, tuberculosis, or multiple sclerosis."
